social_posts.post_text: Thank you everyone for the birthday wishes! I am so thankful and praise God for this birthday and many more to follow as I am a cancer survivor.  Year 44 was not what I expected.  I was diagnosed with breast cancer in March and had a double mastectomy with reconstruction in May.  I am now cancer free!!!! I am sharing this to remind everyone to GET CHECKED EVERY YEAR! Please go to the doctor!!! I did not have any lumps or symptoms.  I was living my best life.  Little did I know I had something going on.  So thankful for my husband as he had to deal with me and my emotions on a daily basis.  Also, thanks to my family, friends, and doctors that helped me through ❤️ 🙌🏾

So we get to the meet in Hungary and we arrive in the warm up area. She sees small training hurdles said can I play with them. I explained to her how we used to do speed work with high and low hurdles.  She asked to try. Tell me why she hurdled for hours. I had to make her stop and rest. Now she wants to run track and play tennis. This was her first time trying and I showed her a few drills. Not too many because my body said “ABSOLUTELY NOT” 😂😂 I haven’t tried to hurdle anything in 12 years. Great moment to share with my daughter. She was so happy. #athlete #hurdles #kids #fun
She had to get some McDonalds fries in Europe to see if there is a difference. She said it tastes better over here. It’s real potatoes 😂
